\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q3.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 A shop that sells items through a website uses a relational database to store information about the products that it sells and the sales that it has made.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The figure below shows the structure of the relations in the database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1701\ri567 Product(\ul ProductID\ul0 , Description, QuantityInStock, SupplierID)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 Sale(\ul SaleID\ul0 , CustomerID, SaleDate)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 SaleLine(\ul SaleID\ul0 , ProductID, QuantitySold)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 Customer(\ul CustomerID\ul0 , Forename, Surname, EmailAddress)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 Supplier(\ul SupplierID\ul0 , SupplierName, SupplierEmail)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Product relation stores information about the products that the shop sells and who supplies them. Each type of product is identified by a unique number and has a brief description. For example, ProductID 1 has the Description \u8216?A4 Ring Binder \u8211? Purple\u8217?. The QuantityInStock indicates how many of the product the shop currently has in stock.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Sale and SaleLine relations are used to record the details of the sale of products to a customer. Each sale is identified by a unique SaleID, which is a number.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Customer relation stores the details of customers who have registered on the website so that they can purchase products. Each customer is identified by a unique CustomerID, which is a number.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Supplier relation records the details of companies who supply the products to the shop. Each supplier is identified by a unique SupplierID, which is a number.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 When a sale is made to a customer, three changes need to be made to the data in the database:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~a new record is created in the Sale table\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~a new record is created in the SaleLine table for each different product that is part of the sale\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~the records in the Product table are updated to reduce the QuantityInStock by the purchased quantity for each type of product that has been sold.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 A sale is made on the 29/09/2024 to the Customer with CustomerID 48. The sale is for 3 of the products with ProductID 1. The sale is to be given the SaleID 4072.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The database system can be accessed by many users simultaneously.\par
