\f1\fs20\cf0\b\ltrpar\qr\sb60\sa0\li0\ri0 (5)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (b)\u8195?\~The cinema had to be closed on the 29th March 2023 so that some maintenance could take place.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 The SQL query in \b Figure 2\b0  was written to delete all of the showings on this date. Some errors were made in the query.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0 Figure 2\par
\f2\fs20\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li2268\ri567 DELETE\par
\f2\fs20\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li2268\ri567 FROM Showing, Film\par
\f2\fs20\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li2268\ri567 WHERE ShowDate = 29/03/2023\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 Describe \b two\b0  errors that have been made in the query.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 Do \b not\b0  refer to the use of semi-colons in your response.\par
