\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q7.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 A sports centre uses a relational database to store information about its facilities (such as the swimming pool) and the bookings that have been made to use them.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The code below shows the structure of the relations in the database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1701\ri567 Facility(\ul FacilityID\ul0 , Description, MaxPeople, PricePerHour)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 FacilityForSport(\ul Sport\ul0 , \ul FacilityID\ul0 )\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 Booking(\ul FacilityID\ul0 , \ul BookingDate\ul0 , \ul StartTime\ul0 , EndTime, CustomerID)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567 Customer(\ul CustomerID\ul0 , Forename, Surname, EmailAddress)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Facility relation stores the different facilities available at the sports centre. Each one is identified by a unique number and has a brief description. For example, the facility with FacilityID 1 has the description \u8216?Outdoor Pitch A\u8217?. PricePerHour is the price of hiring a facility for 1 hour. For example, the facility with FacilityID 1 has a price per hour of \'a317.50.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The FacilityForSport relation identifies which facilities are suitable for which sports. For example, the facility with FacilityID 1 is suitable for football, rugby and hockey and would therefore require three separate records in this relation.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Booking relation stores the bookings that have been made. Bookings must start and end either on the hour, at quarter past, half past or quarter to the hour. A customer can make bookings for more than one facility for the same time. For example, a badminton club secretary might book both of the indoor sports halls for the same time. However, each facility can only be booked by one customer at any one time.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Customer relation stores the details of customers who have made bookings.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a)\u8195?\~The entity identifier (primary key) for the Booking relation is a composite entity identifier, consisting of these three attributes:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\fi0 FacilityID, BookingDate, StartTime\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 An alternative entity identifier could have been chosen, composed of different attributes.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 Shade \b one\b0  lozenge to indicate which of the following groups of attributes would form a valid alternative entity identifier for the Booking relation.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li0\ri0 \~\par

