\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q8.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 An estate agency makes details of the properties that it has for sale available to potential customers through a website. The details of the properties and other data that are useful to the agency are stored in a relational database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The individual web pages about specific properties that a customer can view are generated dynamically by a program from the data in the database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 A client-server system, which uses CRUD and REST, is used to provide details of properties in a web page that is being viewed in a web browser on a client computer.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Figure 1\b0  shows the structure of the relations in the database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0 Figure 1\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li2268\ri567\fi-567 Property(\ul PropertyID\ul0 , HouseNum, Street, Area, Postcode, Bedrooms, Bathrooms, AskingPrice, SellerID)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li2268\ri567\fi-567 Seller(\ul SellerID\ul0 , Title, Forename, Surname, Telephone)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li2268\ri567\fi-567 Buyer(\ul BuyerID\ul0 , Title, Forename, Surname, Telephone, DesiredArea, MinBedrooms, MaxPrice)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li2268\ri567\fi-567 Viewing(\ul BuyerID, PropertyID, ViewingDate\ul0 , ViewingTime)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li2268\ri567\fi-567 Sale(\ul SaleID\ul0 , PropertyID, BuyerID, SalePrice)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Property relation stores details of the properties that are for sale. This includes the number of bedrooms and the number of bathrooms that a property has.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Seller relation stores details of people who are selling the properties.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~The Buyer relation stores details of the people who are looking to buy a property and information about the type of property they want, including the area that they want to live in, the minimum number of bedrooms that they need in a property and the maximum price that they are prepared to pay.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~An entry is made in the Viewing relation whenever a buyer arranges to look at a property.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~An entry is made in the Sale relation whenever a property is sold to a buyer. The SalePrice may be different to the AskingPrice for the property.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a)\u8195?\~The list below contains four statements about the principles of CRUD and REST. One of these statements is false.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 Shade \b one\b0  lozenge to indicate which statement is \b false\b0 .\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li0\ri0 \~\par

