\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 Viewing(\ul BuyerID, PropertyID, ViewingDate\ul0 , ViewingTime)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 Sale(\ul SaleID\ul0 , PropertyID, BuyerID, SalePrice)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (e)\u8195?\~Write an SQL query that will retrieve from the database the list of all properties that the buyer with BuyerID 23 might be interested in buying. The properties should:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~be in the buyer\u8217?s desired area\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~have at least the minimum number of bedrooms the buyer requires\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~cost no more than the maximum price that the buyer is prepared to pay.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 The list of properties returned should only include, for each property, the following details:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~the PropertyID\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~the street that the property is on\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~the number of bedrooms that the property has\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1701\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~the asking price for the property.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 The list should be ordered with the most expensive property at the top of the list and the least expensive at the bottom of the list.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 ___________________________________________________________________\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567 ___________________________________________________________________\par
