\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q10.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 A veterinary practice with four different surgeries intends to use a relational database box to store the data that it needs to manage its business.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Customers of the practice are pet owners who bring their pets to one of the surgeries for appointments. The surgeries are staffed by vets.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Each customer is identified by a unique identity number and the customer\u8217?s forename, surname and telephone number are recorded.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Each pet is identified by a unique identity number and the pet\u8217?s name, type and date of birth are recorded.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Each surgery is identified uniquely by its name. The town in which it is located and the surgery\u8217?s telephone number are recorded.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Each vet is identified by a unique identity number and the vet\u8217?s forename and surname are recorded.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 A pet is owned by one or more customers and each customer may own any number of pets. Over their lifetimes, pets may attend many appointments.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 To make an appointment for a pet, a customer contacts a surgery. The appointment is made for the pet to take place on a particular date and time at a specific surgery.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 Each vet is associated with one surgery which they work at; each surgery is staffed by several vets.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a)\u8195?\~Complete the entity-relationship diagram below for a \b fully normalised\b0  relational database to store the data required by the veterinary practice.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 Some of the entities and relationships have been drawn for you. You need to draw the remaining \b three\b0  entities and clearly show the relationships between the entities and their degree.\par
\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0{\pict\jpegblip\picw6225\pich2895\picwgoal6225\pichgoal2895\picscalex100\picscaley100
}\~\par
\f1\fs20\cf0\b\ltrpar\qr\sb60\sa0 (3)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (b)\u8195?\~Develop a \b fully normalised design\b0  for a relational database to store the information required by the veterinary practice. To help you, the Pet, Surgery and Vet relations have already been defined in \b Figure 1\b0 .\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b\ltrpar\qc\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\fi0 Figure 1\par
