\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Job (\ul JobID\ul0 , CarRegNo, JobDate, InGarage, JobDuration)\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Car (\ul CarRegNo\ul0 , Make, Model, OwnerName, OwnerEmail, OwnerTelNo)\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 Part (\ul PartID\ul0 , Description, Price, QuantityInStock)\par
\intbl\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb90\sa90\li45\ri45 PartUsedForJob (\ul JobID, PartID\ul0 , QuantityUsed)
\intbl \cell\pard\intbl\row\pard
\pard
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Each car has a unique CarRegNo.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~A type of car can be uniquely identified by the combination of its Make and Model. Different Makes may use the same Model name and a particular manufacturer (Make) will produce several different car Models.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~A booking made for a car on a particular date counts as one job, regardless of how many different tasks are completed upon it.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~A job might require the use of any number of parts, including zero.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8226?\u8195?\u8195?\~Some of the details are stored in the database as soon as a booking is made and others are only added when a job has been completed.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 The attribute JobID is the Entity Identifier (Primary Key) of the Job relation.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a)\~\~\~\~\~If the JobID attribute were not included in the Job relation, which other attribute or attributes that are currently in the relation could probably be used as an Entity Identifier (Primary Key) instead?\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 ___________________________________________________________________\par
\f1\fs20\cf0\b\ltrpar\qr\sb60\sa0\li0\ri0 (1)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 It has been suggested that the owner details (OwnerName, OwnerEmail, OwnerTelNo) should not be stored in the Car relation and that a new relation should be created to store owner details separately from car details.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (b)\~\~\~\~\~Explain why storing the owner details separately would improve the design of the database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi0 ___________________________________________________________________\par
