\f1\fs27\cf1\ltrpar\ql\sb450\sa45\li150\ri45 Q15.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\b0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li567\ri567 A company is building an e-commerce website. The website will display details of the products that the company sells and allow customers to place orders. Customers must register on the website before they can place an order and each order can be for one or more different products.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The product, customer and order details will be stored in a relational database.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 It was originally proposed that the following three relations were required:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8195?\u8195?\~Product(\ul ProductNumber\ul0 , ProductPrice, ProductDescription, QuantityInStock)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8195?\u8195?\~Order(\ul OrderNumber\ul0 , OrderDate, CustomerID, OrderingComputerIPAddress, ProductNumber, Quantity)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8195?\u8195?\~Customer(\ul CustomerID\ul0 , CustomerName, Address, Postcode, EmailAddress, PaymentCardNumber)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567\fi0 The computer programmer identified a problem with the Order relation and stated that it should be divided up into two separate relations:\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8195?\u8195?\~Order(\ul OrderNumber\ul0 , OrderDate, CustomerID, OrderingComputerIPAddress)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 \u8195?\u8195?\~OrderLine(\ul OrderNumber, ProductNumber\ul0 , Quantity)\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a)\~\~\~\~\~Describe the problem that the programmer identified with the original Order relation and explain what the cause of this problem was.\par
