\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 When an athlete is entered into a race, a record of the entry is created in the RaceEntryAndResult table. Initially, the TimeSet is recorded as 00:00.00 (meaning 0 minutes, 0 seconds, 0 hundredths of a second) to indicate that the race has not yet been run. After the race has been run, if the athlete successfully completes it, then their TimeSet value is updated to record the time that they achieved in minutes, seconds and hundredths of a second. The TimeSet value remains at 00:00.00 for athletes who fail to complete the race.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li567\ri567 The primary keys in the Athlete and Race relations have been identified in \b Figure 1\b0  by underlining them. The correct primary key for the RaceEntryAndResult relation has not been identified.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb240\sa0\li1134\ri567\fi-567 (a) \~\~\~\~In \b Figure 2\b0  below, underline the appropriate attribute name(s) to identify the correct primary key for this relation.\par
\f1\fs22\cf0\ltrpar\ql\sb0\sa0\li0\ri0\fi0 \~\par

